        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 2:22PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 222 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
southwestern Abilene, moving northwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southwestern Abilene, Tye, Hawley, Caps, and Dyess Afb.

This includes Interstate 20 between Mile Markers 273 and 284.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
